Section.Content:
The Beatles: Discography and Filmography
Studio Albums
Please Please Me (1963)
• Release Date: March 22, 1963
• Key Tracks: "I Saw Her Standing There," "Love Me Do," "Please Please Me"
• Description: The Beatles' debut album that captured their early rock 'n' roll sound and
youthful energy.
With The Beatles (1963)
• Release Date: November 22, 1963
• Key Tracks: "All My Loving," "Money (That's What I Want)," "It Won't Be Long"
• Description: Their second album, showcasing a blend of original compositions and covers.
A Hard Day's Night (1964)
• Release Date: July 10, 1964
• Key Tracks: "A Hard Day's Night," "Can't Buy Me Love," "And I Love Her"
• Description: Soundtrack album for their first feature film, capturing the frenzy of
Beatlemania.
Beatles for Sale (1964)
• Release Date: December 4, 1964
• Key Tracks: "Eight Days a Week," "I'll Follow the Sun," "Baby's in Black"
• Description: Reflective of their exhausting schedule, mixing rock 'n' roll with introspective
ballads.
Help! (1965)
• Release Date: August 6, 1965
• Key Tracks: "Help!," "Ticket to Ride," "Yesterday"
• Description: Soundtrack to their second film, showing a transition to more mature
songwriting.
Rubber Soul (1965)
• Release Date: December 3, 1965
• Key Tracks: "Norwegian Wood (This Bird Has Flown)," "In My Life," "Michelle"
• Description: Marked a shift towards introspective lyrics and experimental studio
techniques.

Revolver (1966)
• Release Date: August 5, 1966
• Key Tracks: "Eleanor Rigby," "Tomorrow Never Knows," "Yellow Submarine"
• Description: Innovative and eclectic album, pushing the boundaries of studio production.
Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band (1967)
• Release Date: June 1, 1967
• Key Tracks: "Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds," "A Day in the Life," "With a Little Help
from My Friends"
• Description: Iconic concept album that revolutionized music with its thematic unity and
production techniques.
Magical Mystery Tour (1967)
• Release Date: November 27, 1967
• Key Tracks: "Strawberry Fields Forever," "Penny Lane," "All You Need Is Love"
• Description: Soundtrack to their psychedelic television film, blending music and visual
artistry.
The Beatles (White Album) (1968)
• Release Date: November 22, 1968
• Key Tracks: "Back in the U.S.S.R.," "While My Guitar Gently Weeps," "Helter Skelter"
• Description: Double album showcasing diverse musical styles and individual songwriting
contributions.
Yellow Submarine (1969)
• Release Date: January 17, 1969
• Key Tracks: "Yellow Submarine," "All Together Now," "It's All Too Much"
• Description: Soundtrack to the animated film, featuring both new and previously released
tracks.
Abbey Road (1969)
• Release Date: September 26, 1969
• Key Tracks: "Come Together," "Something," "Here Comes the Sun"
• Description: Last recorded album by The Beatles, known for its medley and iconic cover
image.
Let It Be (1970)
• Release Date: May 8, 1970
• Key Tracks: "Let It Be," "The Long and Winding Road," "Get Back"
• Description: Soundtrack to the documentary film showing the band's tumultuous final days.

Films
A Hard Day's Night (1964)
• Release Date: July 1964
• Description: Directed by Richard Lester, this film captures a fictionalized day in the life of
The Beatles during the height of Beatlemania.
Help! (1965)
• Release Date: July 1965
• Description: Another film directed by Richard Lester, featuring The Beatles in a comedic
adventure with a mix of music and humor.
Magical Mystery Tour (1967)
• Release Date: December 1967
• Description: A surreal television film written and directed by The Beatles, featuring various
musical segments.
Yellow Submarine (1968)
• Release Date: July 1968
• Description: An animated musical film inspired by The Beatles' music, known for its
psychedelic visuals and storytelling.
Let It Be (1970)
• Release Date: May 1970
• Description: A documentary film directed by Michael Lindsay-Hogg, showcasing The
Beatles during the recording of their album "Let It Be."
